.SH NAME
EventSource.close \- EventSource: close() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]close()\f[B]\f[R] method of the \f[CR]EventSource\f[R]
interface closes the connection, if one is made, and sets the
\f[CR]EventSource.readyState\f[R] attribute to \f[CR]2\f[R] (closed).
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] If the connection is already closed, the method does
nothing.
.RE
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
close()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SH EXAMPLES
